@NODE how2editmerrymen "How to edit merry-men?"

To edit Merry-men hit the @{B}AMIGA + 3@{UB} combination or choose
"Mode->Edit Merrymen" from Menu. Now you can edit merry-men and their routes.
The merry-men are presented by a yellow squares with a number inside. Once
the merry-men is selected by mouse its route if exists is shown on map with
white circles with a number inside. Use mouse to move these items.
Double-click to enter properties.

The Merry-Men can be either Colour or Gray and can be directed Left or Right.

The route node has following attributes:

Action         - which action to perform once reached the target
   Move        - just move to next point
   Wait        - wait on specific trigger
   End         - end route
   Enter       - enter the gate
   Fix         - fix the device and activate trigger
   Fill        - fill the inventory with item
   Beam        - teleport (Techno Treat world)
   Flush       - flush the inventory
   Do          - do some special action
   Set         - set a specific trigger
Item           - which item to fill when moving to the target
Trigger        - trigger number associated with action
Value          - special value, for triggers always use 255 here
Face           - which direction to face upon target
Throw          - whether the merry-men need to be thrown by the hero

And finally some special checkboxes:

No return      - whether the merry-men should return when meeting obstacle
Skip ladders   - whether the merry-men should skip ladders
Push button    - whether the merry-men should push button
Instant turn   - whether the merry-men should turn instantly when falling
Enter pipe     - whether the merry-men should enter pipe (Techno Treat)

@ENDNODE
@NODE triggers "How the triggers works?"

The triggers are basicly a switches which changes the state of the object's
@{B}property@{UB}. But this is not the whole truth. The triggers can be
used by many other things like merry-men to communicate with each other.
There are 30 triggers available per map for the user.

Example of use of a trigger:

To make a lever<->platform connection add these objects to map then enter
platform's properties. Now select checkbox next to State property. This will
assign a trigger to this property. Note the number which appear next to
checkbox - this will be our trigger number. Now enter the number 1 in the
text field and exit platform's properties. Now enter the lever's properties
and type our trigger number in the Trigger field of the lever. And it's done!

