@NODE whatsnew "What's new in v2.0?"

What's new in version 2.0?

1. New IFF map format which stores additional data for maps.
2. Object properties are now all named and easily configured.
3. Objects, Merry-men and their Route nodes are now presented in graphics
   form and can be selected and moved by mouse.
   Their properties can be edited by double-clicking on them.
4. Triggers can be assigned to properties in object property editor.
5. The map is drawn much faster and eats less graphics memory.
6. The graphics data is reduced to minimum.
7. The data about objects is imported from external files.

@ENDNODE

@NODE whatsmissing "What's missing in version 2.0?"

The object database in current version contains less than 50 objects
which is insufficient to make maps for all worlds. For now only Underworld
and Tombs of Egypt worlds are supported which is a subject to change
(the program is ready to support the rest of the worlds).

Additionally there is no possibility to define sky and water. All these
features will appear in next release.

